                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12528020" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 17 Sep 2007 11:00:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Refactored how binding the services works: The bound services are acquired only when the bind or unbind method(s) require&lt;br/&gt;
the service object. Otherwise, in case of the (un)bind taking a service reference, the service object is not retrieved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nevertheless, an entry in the map of bound services is created when binding the service to ensure the unbind method is called when the service is unregistered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed in Rev. 576362&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12529436" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 21 Sep 2007 14:24:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Deployed new snapshot build containing this fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12601208" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 30 May 2008 18:11:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This may be closed by now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
